Here’s a basic example of creating a rounded rectangle with CSS:

css
.rounded-rectangle {
  width: 100px;
  height: 60px;
  background-color: #ccc;
  border-radius: 10px;
}


In this snippet, `border-radius` is used to create rounded corners, which is a common technique in CSS art for shaping elements.

You can add a gradient background using the `background` property with either linear or radial gradients. For example:

css
.koala-element {
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #a8a8a8, #7a7a7a);
}


This creates a vertical gradient from light gray to dark gray, which can give elements a more three-dimensional or textured appearance.
